post_text:
Allen Bowden will be following the guidelines developed by the Oklahoma State Board Of Education. At this time, the district is making the final preparations for students to return to campus. The staff is excited to get our students back and this school year underway. We will attempt to have in-person class for as long as it's safe to do so.

Due to the nature of the COVID-19 virus, nothing is certain; however, our best efforts will be given to have school in a safe and protected environment.

Our students are scheduled to return on 8/27/2020. The district will be requiring students and staff to wear masks while on the bus and on campus. You can find the full list of guidelines on the school website. Click on About Us>Documents. Once there, look for the ABS Return to Learn Plan. Thanks!

post_text:
***ATTENTION!***

Next Thursday, May 14th, is student items pickup day. This is the ONLY day scheduled, so please make arrangements for someone to pick up your child‚Äôs locker items and end-of-year packet.

Directions are as follows:
Go through the elementary car line, give names of all students, and wait for delivery of the bagged items to your car. This is to minimize exposure for all parties involved.

Times are as follows:
Students whose last names begin with A-L will pick up 10am-noon, and students whose last names begin with M-Z will pick up noon-2pm.

Families with multiple students with differing last names need only choose one timeframe; ALL students‚Äô items/packets will be delivered together.

Again, these are the ONLY times we will do this. We must abide by CDC and SDEOK guidelines and reduce time on campus.

Finally, you will be notified when yearbooks are available if you ordered one.

We look forward to seeing and serving you on Thursday, May 14th! Thanks so much for your support and understanding!

Since StuCo‚Äôs Spirit Week was cancelled due to the COVID-19 school closure, we thought a Virtual Spirit Week (4/20-4/24) would be a fun alternative! Parents/Families and teachers/staff are encouraged to participate! First and foremost, please follow social distancing guidelines. Here are the other rules:

1. Wait for the day‚Äôs post on our official page.
2. Make certain your photograph is school appropriate.
3. Share your picture in the comments of that day‚Äôs post (students need PERMISSION from a parent/guardian).

It‚Äôs that simple! Get ready to show off your creativity AND your school spirit! Check out this overview of the week‚Äôs endeavors!

Exciting news! üéâ We have partnered with OETA to provide in-home learning opportunities for students. The goal is to bring parents, students and teachers together with content and curriculum to meet educational needs while schools are closed due to coronavirus.

Beginning Monday, March 30, OETA will be adjusting its daytime schedule to provide curriculum-based programming for students over the air on its broadcast channel, OETA WORLD. Programs will include PBS favorites like NOVA, Nature, American Experience and PBS KIDS programming.

Programming changes to OETA WORLD will take place Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. until 6 p.m. until the end of the school year.

Teachers and parents are encouraged to visit OETA.tv/LearningAtHome to view an updated program schedule, OETA‚Äôs statewide channel list, curriculum and activities.

post_text:
We will begin serving grab-n-go meals on Tuesday, 3/24. Every child, 18 years and younger, can get both a breakfast and lunch meal bag each day. Children MUST BE present in the car in order to receive the meals. Children DO NOT have to be students of Allen Bowden in order to receive the meals.

We will open our gates on the NORTH end of the campus to conduct a drive-thru. Please stay in your vehicle and receive the meals through the vehicle window. Meals will be served from 10am-11am on what would be normal school days. Both meals, breakfast and lunch, will be given at the same time. We appreciate your good will and patience as we continue to develop and/or update this plan as necessary.

post_text: The original plan concerning the teacher walkout was 5 days. Allen Bowden will stick to that plan. We will NOT have school next week, April 2-6, in order to allow our teachers to be at the Capitol to say thank you but to advocate for further educational funding. Kids will be back in school on Monday, April 9th. We will add five days to the end of the calendar, therefore, the last day of school will be Monday, May 14th.
